    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"rigorous\" is a pretty strong word for it, but it's harder to ignore the actual words on the page compared to just interpreting what society \"needs\" now. if you start changing the meaning of the text every time political winds shift, aren't you basically just saying there is no actual law, just whatever judges decide is best at the time? it feels like the \"living constitution\" idea is just a polite way to justify judicial activism. can't you see why a lot of people would say that approach is fundamentally undermining the rule of law?",
